te arguments is necessary for the better participation of all citizens in a modern democracy. Even more so in&nbsp;\u03bfur times when democracy and its institutions&nbsp;&nbsp;seem to be often in crisis and under attack by autocratic ideologies worldwide.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, the method of analysing&nbsp;&nbsp;the quality of arguments that Prof. Brewer has developed and will&nbsp;&nbsp;expand on during his presentation here is valuable not only for every lawyer but also for every active citizen.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, I would like to congratulate our Lecturer Dr. Konstantinos Tsinas for the initiative&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;organizing these events and for inviting Professor Brewer. Dr. Tsinas himself specializes, among other things, in legal philosophy and legal argumentation and is an astute legal thinker. We are very proud to have him in our department.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Brevity is the soul of wit, so I do not wish to take more of your time.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I am looking forward to attending Prof. Brewer\u2019s lecture.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you very much.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>7 June 2023, 18.00, Room \u0392108, University House &#8220;Anastasio&#8217;s G. Leventis&#8221;, University of Cyprus, 1 Panepistimiou Avenue, Aglantzia. Welcome note by Costas Paraskeva Associate Professor of Public Law and Human Rights Chairman of the Department of Law, University of Cyprus Distinguished guests, Dear colleagues, Dear students, It is with great pleasure that I am addressing &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"https:\/\/cparaskeva.com\/2023\/06\/08\/public-lecture-by-professor-scott-brewer-from-harvard-law-school-can-we-be-equal-and-excellent-too-answers-from-the-logocrat-agon-axic-method\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Public Lecture by Professor Scott Brewer from Harvard Law School, &#8220;Can We be Equal and Excellent Too? Answers from the Logocrat-Agon-Axic Method&#8221;, University